title: Bug 6322 - All Types Dialog Shows Obfuscated Classes
description: This bug report addresses the issue where the 'All Types' dialog displays obfuscated classes from JDK 1.4, including 'a,' 'a1,' 'b,' 'c,' 'd,' etc.
OB: The observed behavior is that these obfuscated classes are prominently listed in the 'Open Type' dialog.
EB: The expected behavior is not clearly defined in the bug report. However, it is reasonable to expect that obfuscated classes should not be prominently listed in the 'Open Type' dialog.
SR: Steps to reproduce the issue are missing in the bug report. To provide a comprehensive report, it would be helpful to include detailed steps to reproduce the problem.
